§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $x ∈ 𝗥^d$. ⦉

  ‖ The ❬open ball❭ centered at $x$ (or around $x$) of radius
    $δ > 0$ is the set
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \Set*{y ∈ 𝗥^{d}}{d(x, y) < δ} ⦉
    ⦉
    where $d: 𝗥^d ×𝗥^d → 𝗥$ is the usual Euclidean distance. ⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We sometimes denote the open ball by $B(x,δ)$ or $B_{δ}(x)$ ⦉
⦉

